<!DOCTYPE html>
<html lang="en">
<head>
    <meta charset="UTF-8">
    <meta name="viewport" content="width=device-width, initial-scale=1.0">
    <title>404 Not Found</title>
    <style>
        @import url('https://fonts.googleapis.com/css2?family=JetBrains+Mono&display=swap');
        * {
            font-family: 'Jetbrains Mono', monospace;
        }
        body {
            background-color: #F4F5FA;
        }
        div{
            margin-left: 2rem;
        }
        b {
            margin-left: 1rem;
        }
    </style>
</head>
<body>
    <h1>404 Not Found</h1>
    <p>The page you are looking for does not exist.</p>
    
    <h2>Guide</h2>
    <div>
        <h3>1. EJS Templates</h3>
        <p>Put your EJS files in the <code>views</code> directory. For example:</p>
        <pre>
        views/
        ├── home.ejs
        ├── about.ejs
        └── contact.ejs</pre>
        <p>Access these pages via 
            <br><b>http://localhost:3000/home</b>
            <br><b>http://localhost:3000/about</b>
            <br><b>http://localhost:3000/contact</b>
        </p>
        
        <h3>2. Public Files</h3>
        <p>Place static files like CSS, JavaScript, and images in the <code>public</code> directory. For example:</p>
        <pre>
        public/
        ├── css/
        │   └── main.css
        └── js/
            └── app.js</pre>
        <p>Access these files directly via
            <br><b>http://localhost:3000/public/css/main.css</b>
            <br><b>http://localhost:3000/public/js/app.js</b>
        </p>
    </div>
</body>
</html>
